Ad M. Caes. ii. 1 (Naber, p. 25).

<Domino meo.>? 1. | Posterioribus litteris tuis, cur orationem in senatu non recitaverim, requisisti. At ego et edicto 1 For Cod. Thucydides. Jerome quotes the words as from Theoph., but they occur also in Plato, Legg. v. 731 B.- 2 The title is left blank. This letter follows in the Codex

