3. So much more fortunate am I than was Her- cules or Achilles, for their armour and weapons were

_ borne by Philoctetes and Patroclus, men far inferior _ to them in manhood, while my poor, not to say sorry,

speech has been rendered famous by Caesar the most learned and eloquent of all men. Never was scene

