As far as I am concerned, the writing is finished —so send me something else to write—but my secretary was not at hand to copy out what I wrote. However, what I wrote was not to my mind, as I was hurried, and your being poorly took a good deal out of me. But I will ask your indulgence to- morrow, when I send it. Farewell, my sweetest of masters. The Lady my mother sends you greeting.

