T : ? 154-156 a.p. o my Lord.

This is the third day that I have been troubled all night long with griping in the stomach and diarrhoea. Last night, indeed, I suffered so much that I have not been able to go out, but am keeping my bed. The doctors recommend a bath. I have prayed the Gods to give you many happy returns of the day.* Farewell, my Lord. Greet your Lady.

? Ehrenthal thinks that Marcus should have said: ‘‘ We too love you the more because Gratia is like you. So we can understand how our likeness to our baby endears us to you.” 3 April 26 (? 156).

