I count heavy? I would not traffic in anything nor buy anything, that necessitated an equivalent re- turn passing, as they say, from house to house. Consider this point also, what pleasure acceptance gives the sender, and what mortification follows upon non-acceptance . . . . even after many days to come to you. Pray believe that the law of Gods and cities and friends is a just one... . but as friends do not parade such a forwardness of good- will but from diffidence conceal it, I send before you give permission. Do not you send back my gift a second time, as you ought not to have done even the first time.

To AppiaAN From Fronto.

